race.comment: WOKOU (12) ran below expectations last time after being in contention on the turn at Armidale, finishing tenth and beaten 11 lengths starting at $10. Beautifully placed and is sure to take plenty of stopping. BRAZEN BRANDO (4) resumed three weeks ago over 1000m at Port Macquarie and was only beaten 1.75 lengths into fourth. Finds a suitable assignment and can get the job done. MISS INDI (8) pushed forward last time and boxed on to finish 1.1 lengths away in third over 1106m at Grafton. Will be up on the speed from the low draw. Has the talent to build on that strong effort last start. TYPHOON NETA (7) showed good early speed from the inside draw last time and stalked the lead before fading to finish fourth over 1200m at Port Macquarie. Sure to give a sight.
